description:
Cont closures store captures as Tagged today (forcing tag-on-store + untag-on-load round-trips even when the capture's type is statically known). Match the lambda-closure path: store captures in their typed repr.

Touch src/ir_codegen.rs:

1. Term::Call cont-closure builder (≈line 3439): currently
     let from = var_repr(cv.0, &raw_int_vars, &raw_f64_vars);
     let v = coerce_to(.., cap_vals[i], from, ArgRepr::Tagged);
   Replace ArgRepr::Tagged with param_reprs[cont_sid as usize][i + 1] (capture index i is fz_param i+1 since fz_param[0] is the result).

2. Term::CallClosure cont-closure builder (≈line 3792): same change.

3. Term::Receive cont-closure builder (search for the Receive site): same change. Receive's cont has param_reprs[0] = Tagged (forced) but param_reprs[1..] (captures) can be typed.

4. compile_fn cont-fn entry harness capture load (≈line 2956): currently
     let off = HEADER_SIZE + SLOT_BYTES * 2 + ((i - 1) as i32) * SLOT_BYTES;
     let tagged_v = b.ins().load(types::I64, MemFlags::trusted(), self_val, off);
     let v = coerce_to(.., tagged_v, ArgRepr::Tagged, my_param_reprs[i]);
   Replace with a typed load:
     let cl_ty = my_param_reprs[i].cl_type();
     let v = b.ins().load(cl_ty, MemFlags::trusted(), self_val, off);
     (no coerce — the producer stored in my_param_reprs[i]'s repr per .1)

Lambda (closure-target) capture path already does typed load (line ≈2986) — this aligns cont fns with the same convention.

Acceptance:
- A fixture where a cont captures a typed int (e.g. a chained add) shows the capture stored and loaded WITHOUT tag/untag.
- cargo test --workspace green.
- §8 fixtures pass on all three paths.
